Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.11,0:00:10.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, their level's really going up...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:13.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's just what I'd expect to see \Nfrom the Black Sword Knights,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akihabara's most macho guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.06,0:00:17.62,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is what happens when I get serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.91,0:00:20.44,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,You really are amazing, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.44,0:00:22.50,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,You keep making the knights stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.73,0:00:28.02,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Both you and Reserick are \Nirreplaceable to Maihama now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.41,0:00:32.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you've complimented us, \Nwe can work even harder, Lord Iselus.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.77,0:00:34.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.79,0:00:39.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're working hard, aren't you, Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.20,0:00:44.02,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to stop that crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.65,0:02:19.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,About that lunar communication device \Nyou asked me for yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.58,0:02:22.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to cost that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.32,0:02:23.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Given its scale, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:27.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Even three years of Akihabara's total \Nbudget wouldn't be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.10,0:02:29.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Three years...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:31.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to say it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.04,0:02:36.76,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,but even if we complete it, getting it \Nto work will be another issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.22,0:02:38.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.75,0:02:42.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Still, going back to our original world, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.27,0:02:48.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's difficult, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.10,0:02:50.77,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What did you tell everyone at the Round Table?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.29,0:02:53.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That if we could make contact with the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we might find a hint to getting home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.64,0:03:01.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I told them that I'm not \Nsure going home is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.48,0:03:07.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt they'll approve funds now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:11.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:14.59,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,When you're worried, you get \Nold man wrinkles right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:17.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No wrinkles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:20.21,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:26.60,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1407,1)}Isaac and Iselus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.92,0:03:24.60,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac and Iselus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:32.52,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Um, so what Shiroe said earlier was true, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.84,0:03:35.19,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,A lot is still uncertain,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.19,0:03:38.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,so he said he didn't want us telling anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:41.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,B-But honestly, I don't know to react
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to suddenly hearing that I \Nmight be able to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.60,0:03:46.88,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.10,0:03:52.37,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see my mom and dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.13,0:03:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I want to stay with Nyanta and everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:03:59.38,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to leave you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:00.38,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Serara...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.85,0:04:02.27,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.27,0:04:05.14,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We all got to be such good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:06.39,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.37,0:04:11.50,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.66,0:04:16.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.60,0:04:21.42,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's the natural thing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:24.01,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't make any effort to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.01,0:04:26.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What? Effort?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.29,0:04:29.41,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We were just caught up in this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.72,0:04:30.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.90,0:04:34.38,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I like this place, and I want to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.38,0:04:36.76,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But next time, I want to work hard myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and make my own place to belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:43.30,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:47.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I respect that way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.37,0:04:49.23,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.96,0:04:52.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you have a home, returning to it is natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.83,0:04:55.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I've been expecting to say \Ngoodbye at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.07,0:04:59.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I can respect Tohya's desire \Nto choose on his own,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.62,0:05:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rather than it being a chance event \Nbrought on by outside forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.80,0:05:04.82,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:06.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.85,0:05:09.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu, if you go home,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.23,0:05:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can play music with your father, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:17.92,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but it isn't that simple for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.18,0:05:22.87,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What's the best choice, I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:30.57,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this town seem to be \Nturning into Akihabara lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.80,0:05:32.81,SignA,I,0000,0000,0000,,Deadlines Are Life     {\c&H8966CD&}But I Refuse     {\c&HC99067&}I Can't Go On
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.80,0:05:32.81,SignC,I,0000,0000,0000,,Moe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.57,0:05:35.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it means adventurers are influencing \NPeople of the Land in several ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.81,0:05:36.44,SignA,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HA870D5&\fs22}Cosplay House
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.30,0:05:36.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:38.94,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:40.48,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:42.98,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land are absorbing \Nthe adventurers' culture
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and developing their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.47,0:05:47.45,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,My grandfather said that's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.69,0:05:50.59,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going to keep following us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.59,0:05:54.70,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know a lot about \Nadventurers, like my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.23,0:05:56.71,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Please teach me all sorts of things!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:06:02.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's our job to protect him, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.52,0:06:04.71,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.08,0:06:08.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He really likes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:10.33,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't my style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.33,0:06:12.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:15.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This brings Akihabara and Maihama even closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.90,0:06:19.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But the situation's changed a bit, I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.53,0:06:20.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.16,0:06:22.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:24.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That lunar communication attempt
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.34,0:06:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were talking about at the Round Table.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.38,0:06:30.24,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The one that might give us a \Nhint about how to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:34.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that would change \NYamato's power balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:36.11,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:38.90,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,All that complicated crap irritates me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.90,0:06:41.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What? You don't want to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.04,0:06:45.34,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I try to think about that stuff \Nafter it actually happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.88,0:06:47.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:48.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.91,0:06:51.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That sword's just expensive, not useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.04,0:06:54.30,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Reserick, you should have stopped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.30,0:06:57.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're better at judging swords \Nthan I am, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.50,0:06:59.09,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.00,0:07:04.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Here, buy this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:12.66,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,At my equipment level, I can't master \Nan expensive sword like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.96,0:07:14.23,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not worthy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.23,0:07:15.16,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.26,0:07:20.70,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I was nice enough to recommend it to him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.70,0:07:22.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He knows his own capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:26.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'd thought he was just a child, \Nbut maybe I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.02,0:07:28.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.38,0:07:33.88,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.29,0:07:36.23,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.96,0:07:38.01,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.85,0:07:43.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How is the training going, Sir Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.26,0:07:45.94,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.51,0:07:48.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The knights' levels are rising pretty fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:51.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:54.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,These days, we never know what will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.86,0:07:59.06,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Did you call me here to make small talk, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.44,0:08:01.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's about Iselus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.82,0:08:08.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We will soon be holding a large \Nfestival to celebrate his birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.58,0:08:14.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There, I will announce him \Nas the Cowen family heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.77,0:08:16.97,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Heir? Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.83,0:08:22.76,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought you had a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.76,0:08:24.90,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Feinel married into the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.90,0:08:30.22,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I have complete faith in him, \Nbut the people wouldn't accept that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:34.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They want the heir to have Cowen blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:39.24,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter Salaria and Feinel have three children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.79,0:08:41.67,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The eldest daughter Liseltia,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.67,0:08:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,second-oldest daughter Lenessia, \Nand Iselus, the youngest child.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.77,0:08:50.25,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Liseltia renounced her right to \Nthe throne by getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.73,0:08:53.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves Lenessia and Iselus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:08:54.49,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.49,0:08:56.24,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You have the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.24,0:08:58.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I had never truly seen anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.61,0:09:06.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw Lenessia lose her temper with \Nthe lords, I realized my own foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.14,0:09:11.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I think she is best suited for another job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.75,0:09:14.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Another job, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.58,0:09:18.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, ruling a country is a man's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.44,0:09:21.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Iselus knows that, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.06,0:09:24.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Figuring out the heir is a pain \Non every world, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:29.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, no one can be a ruler \Nunless he understands adventurers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they understand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.31,0:09:33.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Isaac...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.66,0:09:36.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,As you can tell, he is still a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.91,0:09:40.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,While you are in Maihama,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.11,0:09:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will you teach him what we cannot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:54.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy for him to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.16,0:09:58.99,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If there are any other problems, let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.77,0:10:02.35,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell my grandfather without \Nmaking a big deal of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.35,0:10:03.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.70,0:10:10.78,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I thought, if we expanded \Nthis canal, we might be able
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.78,0:10:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to bring stuff in from the port more efficiently...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:21.37,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,This year's strawberries are delicious, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.39,0:10:32.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.75,0:10:41.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was just some rich kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.83,0:10:44.90,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He's really going to be a ruler, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.30,0:10:47.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Lord Iselus?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.99,0:10:50.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a crucial time, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.64,0:10:53.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Things are getting complicated \Nwith Westelande, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.81,0:10:54.88,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Does that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have anything to do with the fact \Nthat Minami's planning something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.09,0:11:01.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's unusually sharp...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.26,0:11:02.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For you, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.96,0:11:05.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.77,0:11:08.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Minami is working with Westelande.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.41,0:11:13.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If they really try to take control of Eastal,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,war will be unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.89,0:11:17.11,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.41,0:11:20.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,In the distant past, it seems
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Westelande Dynasty ruled all of Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.25,0:11:27.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a war that engulfed Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.14,0:11:30.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,After the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:32.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,the dynasty was ultimately destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the land split into its current state,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:36.38,SignB,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs20\fad(322,1)}Holy Empire \NWestelande
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Holy Empire Westelande and the \NLeague of Freedom Cities, Eastal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.38,0:11:39.12,SignB,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs20}Holy Empire                                                 League of Freedom Cities, \NWestelande                                                   Eastal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.90,0:11:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.37,0:11:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Westelande's been saying they're \Nthe true heirs to the dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.08,0:11:47.80,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to profit on the name \Nof a destroyed country?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.80,0:11:49.36,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.53,0:11:54.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Those "annoying" things will occur \Nwhenever many people gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.05,0:11:56.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, with us adventurers involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:12:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd bet the situation now is even more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.55,0:12:02.40,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You know a lot of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:06.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A merchant survives on information.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:07.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.47,0:12:09.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a present for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.88,0:12:11.91,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.25,0:12:17.69,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.37,0:12:20.95,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Both the adventurers and \NPeople of the Land are a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.44,0:12:26.36,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I've always ignored that annoying stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:33.76,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,They're a pain, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:44.83,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they aren't that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:12:58.16,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.72,0:13:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:05.55,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You're small, and this one is lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.20,0:13:08.93,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Once you master it, you'll be a better swordsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.18,0:13:12.30,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,This sword is so expensive, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.30,0:13:13.81,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's your birthday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:14.53,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You can have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.05,0:13:20.94,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't understand \Nthe value of money, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:22.82,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't need it, give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:24.37,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,That was a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.37,0:13:26.00,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.00,0:13:27.70,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.20,0:13:30.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:34.33,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't we going to the princess's place today?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.57,0:13:36.92,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She has her brother's birthday party,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so she says she's returning to Maihama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:40.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Rieze is with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.85,0:13:45.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to talk to her about \Nforming a new idol unit, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:47.51,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,A new unit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.73,0:13:48.34,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.99,0:13:50.66,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A galactic idol unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.66,0:13:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And its name is... Tetnessia!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:55.75,Game Text Left,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(380,1)\an8\c&HFCFCFC&}Tetnessia
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:14:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we do it together, it'll be a surefire hit \Nsince we're both so popular already!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.35,0:14:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do something memorable \Nbefore I go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.37,0:14:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we do a first and final \Nconcert simultaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.96,0:14:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'll be twice as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we show our bare legs on stage, \Nit'll be a big hit for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.43,0:14:14.03,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If we end up going home, we'll have to tell Sia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.90,0:14:15.76,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.76,0:14:18.28,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It will be hard to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.37,0:14:24.52,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Rieze?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.20,0:14:28.48,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to make you do this when you're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.48,0:14:31.40,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,It must be hard, with all the work you have, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.40,0:14:34.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about? I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.74,0:14:38.94,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,But normally, this would be a man's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:43.00,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly... When is that monster \Nin glasses coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:02.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,From an adventurer's perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this nobles' party must seem \Nto make no sense whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.39,0:15:07.74,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.22,0:15:10.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We have banquets and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.46,0:15:13.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And some people have big birthday parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:14.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:18.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Iselus is a smart boy, and he listens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.69,0:15:20.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He understands many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.83,0:15:24.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But he is still only nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.65,0:15:29.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Part of me thinks it's too early to make \Nhim bear such a heavy burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:31.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:35.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Until now, you've carried that heavy \Nburden yourself, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:37.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Until your hair turned white.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.30,0:15:43.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And Iselus may be a kid, but he's a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.60,0:15:45.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A man's job is to take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.10,0:15:49.43,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The weight of your responsibility \Nis equal to the power you possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.99,0:15:53.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And it means you'll have \Nmore people to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.37,0:15:55.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.12,0:15:57.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.27,0:16:00.87,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Given the way he talks to me, he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:03.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.34,0:16:05.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She's as beautiful as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.37,0:16:09.57,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I'm so late, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:13.49,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I'm late, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.22,0:16:16.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.85,0:16:19.34,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late, Iselus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.34,0:16:20.58,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.80,0:16:21.54,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.54,0:16:25.74,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I have more adventurer friends, like you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.60,0:16:31.44,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Iselus, if you think it's that easy to \Nbecome friends with the adventurers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.44,0:16:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're very wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.28,0:16:36.77,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them are monsters and villains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.77,0:16:40.10,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You need to be especially careful \Naround those with glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.41,0:16:42.85,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that, Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.59,0:16:45.60,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:47.11,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.36,0:16:49.42,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,The announcement will be made soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.42,0:16:52.14,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Watch me, Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.43,0:16:53.68,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.48,0:17:20.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Iselus, this is fruit juice from my land.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:21.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:34.03,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.27,0:17:39.03,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, aren't you supposed to be a little \Nmore subtle about assassinations?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.35,0:17:41.54,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.76,0:17:43.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.41,0:17:52.88,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The Roderic lab's special ambush-warning \Nearring is as good as they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.36,0:17:56.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think it would be useful so soon, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.65,0:18:01.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.24,0:18:04.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't breathe it in, Iselus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:06.67,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in our way, adventurer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.46,0:18:09.72,HUD1,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(502,1)\an7}Smoke Bomb \N{\fs18}Effect /Smoke Bomb \N\NBad Statuses: \NMovement speed drop \NAttack speed drop \NDamage over time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:09.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing this for Yamato's peace!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:13.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Reserick, you handle these guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:23.12,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.12,0:18:24.35,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.35,0:18:26.32,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,My legs are just a little numb.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.48,0:18:32.99,Green HUD,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(172,1)\an8}Assassin /Stealth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:35.55,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,They're pretty strong for People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.55,0:18:36.88,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,So those are the—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.55,0:18:47.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Get your hands off the kid, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:50.33,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Sword of Pain Black!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.61,0:18:52.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A bind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:53.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.03,0:18:57.10,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You can't take your eyes off me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:18:59.78,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you lay a finger on Iselus!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:02.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you all on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.16,0:19:20.18,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk about peace when \Nyou're trying to kill a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.92,0:19:22.28,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Morons!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.06,0:19:24.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.45,0:19:25.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That was pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.62,0:19:27.76,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Your debuffs are still in effect. I'll heal you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.15,0:19:29.17,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:31.89,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I was careful not to inhale a lot of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.89,0:19:34.94,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, their \Nlevels aren't normal at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.94,0:19:38.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're the People of the \NLand that Minami is leveling...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.69,0:19:40.22,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:43.01,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Once in a while, your information comes in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.01,0:19:45.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the earring I gave you \Nalso came in handy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.94,0:19:49.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How did you hear about assassins from Westelande?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.18,0:19:53.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A merchant survives on information.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.81,0:19:57.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were more of a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.24,0:20:02.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were more of a musclehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.39,0:20:04.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Iselus,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.99,0:20:07.93,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:09.31,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.31,0:20:12.98,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to stay in this world for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.91,0:20:21.24,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:27.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.59,0:20:29.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know if anything happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.02,0:20:33.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Keep at it, Karashin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.41,0:20:35.59,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.59,0:20:39.37,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our presence is throwing off the balance \Nof the People of the Land's society.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.68,0:20:42.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we have to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.59,0:20:46.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:50.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you half-hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.21,0:20:55.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,My investigations in Susukino \Nhave finally reached an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.81,0:20:57.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Though it came later than expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.31,0:20:59.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for the delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.84,0:21:01.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.29,0:21:02.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.31,0:21:04.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They said to tell you hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.35,0:21:07.66,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What did you find out about the transport gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:10.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As I investigated various matters,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.93,0:21:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found that the fairy rings are \Nrelated to the moon's phases.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.98,0:21:19.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,There's also a legend that there \Nare Alvish ruins on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:24.36,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that the administrator's beacon \Nis deciding the destination coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.92,0:21:26.93,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Just like I thought, the moon's got...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.63,0:21:30.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We need to make contact with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.41,0:21:31.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Contact?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.44,0:21:31.93,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:36.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for a way to return the \Nadventurers to their old world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.86,0:21:40.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,To do that, we must communicate with the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:44.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't seem to be able to create \Nthe communication equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:46.66,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.66,0:21:49.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,There's a facility in Shibuya for that, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.54,0:21:50.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.23,0:21:53.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The remains of the Shibuya TV station,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.25,0:21:55.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,the one communications facility in Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.80,0:21:59.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I investigated it before, \Nbut it's nonfunctional, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.17,0:22:04.72,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But while I investigated the gates, \Nthere was a slight signal from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.72,0:22:06.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose it may still be functioning?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.34,0:22:08.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.42,0:22:11.44,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, villain!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.44,0:22:12.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.89,0:22:14.90,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's collapsing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:16.23,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.18,0:22:18.51,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.51,0:22:19.45,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Explain—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.45,0:22:21.73,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe! Trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.73,0:22:22.98,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The city of Akihabara...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.57,0:24:09.38,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The people fall asleep and will not wake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.38,0:24:11.73,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,At night, a black shadow covers the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.73,0:24:15.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The town of Shibuya has become a \Nraid zone, filled with monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:18.93,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is someone preventing them from \Nreturning to the real world?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.27,0:24:21.20,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe begins the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.20,0:24:24.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But there is an uncertainty within him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Sleep of the Eternal Moth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:30.94,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Sleep of the Eternal Moth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.74,0:24:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have friends to run with me.
